# ── PUBLIC DEPLOY MANIFEST (allowlist) ─────────────────────────────────────
# This file is the OPPOSITE of a normal .gitignore. A normal .gitignore lists
# what to HIDE from git; this one HIDES EVERYTHING, then re-includes ("un-ignores",
# with a leading `!`) ONLY the files we want published. Whatever is allowed here is
# exactly what `git add -A` stages and what the deploy tool pushes to s.4nt.org.
# Everything else — the regenerable *.json data and *.tsv audit files that
# build-public writes next to the pages — stays ignored and never ships.
#
# HOW TO EDIT
#   * Publish a new top-level file:   add   !/<name>
#   * Publish a new page pattern:     add   !**/<name>.html
#   * Stop publishing something:      delete or comment out (#) its `!` line.
#       NOTE: if that file was already committed once, also run
#       `git rm --cached <path>` in this folder — removing the `!` line alone
#       does NOT un-track an already-tracked file.
#   * Directories MUST stay un-ignored (`!*/`, rule 2 below) or git can't descend
#     into them to reach the files (a file can't be re-included while its parent
#     directory is still ignored). See CLAUDE.md "Re-including files under a
#     gitignored directory".
#
# build-public seeds this file once (when missing or still the engine default);
# after that it is YOURS to edit — build-public will not overwrite it.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1. Ignore everything by default.
*

# 2. But let git descend into every subdirectory (so the negations below can
#    reach files nested under the nikaya folders). Without this, **/index.html
#    can never match.
!*/

# 3. The currently-released top-level files.
!/index.html
!/debabel-logo-1k.jpg
!/favicon.png
!/4nt-footer-logo.png
!/CNAME
!/.nojekyll

# 4. Every page, recursively. The public site is one index.html per unit.
!**/index.html
